<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1243</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-003K</addr><route>erct-003K.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>15</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Embedding</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003K.agda" type="external">erct-003K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is called an <em><strong>embedding</strong></em> when for any <tex>x,y:A</tex> the action on identifications <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f } \colon  x=y \to  fx=fy</tex> is <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link>.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1244</anchor>  <addr>erct-003L</addr><route>erct-003L.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Z.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Z" title="Functions and inverses">Functions and inverses</link> › basic definitions</title>  <parent>erct-000Z</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1245</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001Q</addr><route>erct-001Q.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Fiber</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001Q.agda" type="external">erct-001Q.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The <em><strong>fiber</strong></em> of a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> at an element <tex>b:B</tex> is the type consisting of elements <tex>a \colon  A</tex> equipped with identifications <tex>p \colon  fa=b</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1246</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0014</addr><route>erct-0014.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Homotopy</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0014.agda" type="external">erct-0014.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f , g  \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } Bx</tex> be two dependent functions. A <em><strong>homotopy</strong></em> from <tex>f</tex> to <tex>g</tex>, writing <tex>H \colon  f  \sim  g</tex> is given by a dependent function <tex>H \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } fx=gx</tex>. We shall write <tex>1_{ f } \colon  f  \sim  f</tex> for the <em><strong>identity homotopy</strong></em> on <tex>f</tex> defined by <tex>1_{ f } x: \equiv   \mathsf {refl}</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1247</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000Y</addr><route>erct-000Y.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Section-retraction pair</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000Y.agda" type="external">erct-000Y.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>s  \colon  B  \to  A</tex> and <tex>r  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be a pair of maps. A homotopy <tex>h  \colon  r \circ  s  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> exhibits <tex>s</tex> as a <em><strong>section</strong></em> of <tex>r</tex> and <tex>r</tex> as a <em><strong>retraction</strong></em> of <tex>s</tex>. Together, <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( s,r \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> are referred to as a <em><strong>section-retraction pair</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1248</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0025</addr><route>erct-0025.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Retract</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0025.agda" type="external">erct-0025.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>When <tex>s \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a section of <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>, we say that <tex>A</tex> is a <em><strong>retract</strong></em> of <tex>B</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1249</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000U</addr><route>erct-000U.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Biinverse</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000U.agda" type="external">erct-000U.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>biinverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a pair of a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> to <tex>f</tex>. We will refer to a function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> equipped with a biinverse as a <em><strong>biinvertible function</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1250</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000X</addr><route>erct-000X.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Quasi-inverse</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000X.agda" type="external">erct-000X.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>quasi-inverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a function <tex>g  \colon  B  \to  A</tex> equipped with homotopies <tex>\epsilon \colon  f  \circ  g  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> and <tex>\eta \colon  g  \circ  f  \sim 1_{ A }</tex>, rendering <tex>g</tex> simultaneously a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex>.</p><p>Although no coherence laws are assumed for <tex>\eta</tex> and <tex>\epsilon</tex>, we shall refer to them respectively as the <em>unit</em> and <em>counit</em> of the quasi-inverse.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1251</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000W</addr><route>erct-000W.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Inverse</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000W.agda" type="external">erct-000W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>An <em><strong>inverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> equipped with an additional higher coherence <tex>\chi   \colon   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ   \eta   \sim   \epsilon \circ  f</tex> in <tex>f \circ  g  \circ  f  \sim  f</tex> relating the (<em>a priori</em> incoherent) unit and the counit of the quasi-inverse. We will refer to a function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> equipped with an inverse as an <em><strong>invertible function</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1252</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-003K</addr><route>erct-003K.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>15</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Embedding</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003K.agda" type="external">erct-003K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is called an <em><strong>embedding</strong></em> when for any <tex>x,y:A</tex> the action on identifications <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f } \colon  x=y \to  fx=fy</tex> is <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1253</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000V</addr><route>erct-000V.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Equivalence of types</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000V.agda" type="external">erct-000V.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>An <em><strong>equivalence</strong></em> from <tex>A</tex> to <tex>B</tex> is defined to be a function <tex>A  \to  B</tex> equipped with a  <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinverse</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1254</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000W</addr><route>erct-000W.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Inverse</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000W.agda" type="external">erct-000W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>An <em><strong>inverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> equipped with an additional higher coherence <tex>\chi   \colon   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ   \eta   \sim   \epsilon \circ  f</tex> in <tex>f \circ  g  \circ  f  \sim  f</tex> relating the (<em>a priori</em> incoherent) unit and the counit of the quasi-inverse. We will refer to a function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> equipped with an inverse as an <em><strong>invertible function</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1255</anchor> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-004A</addr><route>erct-004A.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embeddings</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-004A.agda" type="external">erct-004A.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> map is an <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embedding</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1256</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   <parent>erct-004A</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-002W" href="erct-002W.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-0049" href="erct-0049.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1257</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-0048</addr><route>erct-0048.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">Embeddings</link> are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0048.agda" type="external">erct-0048.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embedding</link> <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1258</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   <parent>erct-0048</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>We must check that for every <tex>b:B</tex>, the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> at <tex>b</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. Fixing <tex>u_0,u_1: \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, b</tex> we must check that <tex>u_0=u_1</tex>. We let <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a_0,p_0 \right ) \mathclose {} \equiv  u_0</tex> and <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a_1,p_1 \right ) \mathclose {} \equiv  u_1</tex> so that we have <tex>p_0 \colon  fa_0=b</tex> and <tex>p_1 \colon  fa_1=b</tex>. Invoking the <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">path object</link> structure on <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fibers</link> (<ref addr="erct-001R" href="erct-001R.xml" taxon="Example"/>), it suffices to exhibit the following data:</p>
 <tex display="block">    \begin {aligned}     \phi &amp; \colon  a_0 = a_1 \\      \psi &amp; \colon  p_0 =  \mathsf {act}_{ f } \phi \cdot  p_1    \end {aligned}  </tex>

  <p>As <tex>f</tex> is an <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001K" title="Contractible types are propositions">embedding</link>, the map <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f } \colon  a_0 = a_1  \to  fa_0 = fa_1</tex> has an <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverse</link> <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( \mathsf {act}_{ f } ^{-1} , \epsilon , \eta , \chi \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>.</p>

 <p>Let <tex>\alpha   \colon  fa_0 = fa_1</tex> be the concatenation <tex>p_0 \cdot  p_1 ^{-1}</tex>. Therefore we may define:</p>

 <tex display="block">    \begin {aligned}     \phi &amp; \colon  a_0 = a_1 \\      \phi &amp;: \equiv   \mathsf {act}_{ f } ^{-1}   \alpha     \end {aligned}  </tex>

 <p>To define <tex>\psi   \colon  p_0= \mathsf {act}_{ f } \phi \cdot  p_1</tex> we use the counit of our <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverse</link> as we have <tex>\epsilon   \alpha   \colon   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \phi  = p_0 \cdot  p_1 ^{-1}</tex>. Thus concatenating on either side with <tex>p_1</tex> we have our goal, modulo the laws of identification concatenation and symmetry respectively.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1259</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-0049</addr><route>erct-0049.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">Propositional maps</link> are <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embeddings</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0049.agda" type="external">erct-0049.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional map</link> <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is an <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embedding</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1260</anchor> <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   <parent>erct-0049</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Fixing <tex>x,y:A</tex> we must show that <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f } \colon  x = y  \to  fx=fy</tex> is <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link>. By <ref addr="erct-002C" href="erct-002C.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-002D" href="erct-002D.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, it suffices to exhibit a <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinverse</link> to <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f }</tex> (it is convenient that the underlying maps of the <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> and <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> need not be identical).</p>

 <p>We first define the <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> <tex>s_{x,y} \colon  fx = fy  \to  x = y</tex>. Because <tex>f</tex> is assumed to be <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link>, we have by <ref addr="erct-001R" href="erct-001R.xml" taxon="Example"/> an assignment <tex>\phi _{x,y}:  \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }   \mathopen {} \left ( x, \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {} \cong _{ \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} } \mathopen {} \left ( y,h ^{-1} \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>. We therefore define <tex>s_{x,y}h : \equiv   \mathopen {} \left ( \phi _{x,y}h \right ) \mathclose {} .1</tex>; the witness of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sectionhood</link> can be constructed using <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( \phi _{x,y}h \right ) \mathclose {} .2</tex> modulo some identification algebra.</p>

 <p>To construct the <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link> <tex>r_{x,y} \colon  fx=fy \to  x = y</tex>, we note by our assumption that we have an assignment <tex>\psi _{x,y}: \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }   \mathopen {} \left ( x, \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {}  =_{ \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} }  \mathopen {} \left ( y,h ^{-1} \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>, and we define <tex>r_{x,y}h : \equiv   \mathsf {act}_{ -.1 } \mathopen {} \left ( \psi _{x,y}h \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>. It remains to show that for all <tex>x,y:A</tex> and <tex>h \colon  x =y</tex>, we have <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ -.1 } \mathopen {} \left ( \psi _{x,y}h \right ) \mathclose {} =h</tex>. By induction on <tex>h</tex> it suffices to show that for all <tex>x:A</tex> we have <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ -.1 } \mathopen {} \left ( \psi _{x,x} \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {}  =  \mathsf {refl}</tex>. We will deduce that <tex>\psi _{x,x} \mathsf {refl}  =  \mathsf {refl}</tex> from our assumption that <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link> and thus <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">fibred in sets</link> via <ref addr="erct-001L" href="erct-001L.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1261</anchor> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-0047</addr><route>erct-0047.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being an <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embedding</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0047.agda" type="external">erct-0047.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>That a given function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is an <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embedding</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
