</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>1263</anchor> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000K</addr><route>erct-000K.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>3</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Full and faithful <link href="erct-000I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000I" title="Functor between precategories">functor</link></title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000K.agda" type="external">erct-000K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <link href="erct-000I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000I" title="Functor between precategories">functor</link> <tex>F \colon  C  \to  D</tex> is called (<em><strong>full</strong></em>, <em><strong>faithful</strong></em>) when the action on arrows is valued in (<link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjections</link>, <link href="erct-003K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003K" title="Embedding">embeddings</link>) respectively. It is common to refer to a <em>full</em> and <em>faithful</em> functor as <em><strong>fully faithful</strong></em>.</p><p>Fullness and faithfulness are both <em><link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">properties</link></em> of a functor.</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>